=Japanese Narrative Paintings= 
==Literature== 
===PhD Dissertations=== 
* [[Peter Glum]]: The Ban Dainagon Ekotoba, the Kibi Daijin Nitto Emaki, and the Nenju Gyoji Emaki: a reassessment of the evidence for the work of Tokiwa Mitsunaga embodied in two Japanese narrative scroll paintings of the twelfth century, and one presumably close copy. New York University, 1981
* Quitman Phillips: Kano Motonobu and early Kano narrative painting. University of California, 1992

===Monographs=== 
* Dietrich Seckel: Emaki - die Kunst der japanischen Bilderrollen. Zürich: Max Niehans, 1959

===Articles (nonwestern)=== 
* Tetsuhiru KATO: Continous narrative in visual arts: rethinking about the concept of 'ijidouzu'. Kyoto Studies in Aesthetics and Art History. Vol. 10 (2011): 1-39



